resources.string:
Categories range should follow the notation: 'LX:LX' where 'L' refers to the column, while 'X' and 'Y' to the first row and second row enclosing the category values. Examples:
- 'A2:A5' refers to all the cells from the second to the fifth row in the A column;
- 'A2:A' refers to all the cells from the second row onward in the A column;
- 'A:A' refers to all the cells in the A column (it stops at the last value).
